  "response_text": "Losing weight requires a combination of a structured workout plan and a balanced diet. Here’s a simple guide to help you lose 10 pounds over a sustainable period, typically 1 to 2 pounds per week is considered safe and effective. Always consult with a healthcare provider before starting any new diet or exercise program.\n\n### Workout Plan\n\n**Frequency:** Aim for at least 5 days a week.\n\n**Duration:** 30 to 60 minutes per session.\n\n**Types of Workouts:**\n\n1. **Cardiovascular Exercise (3-4 days/week)**\n   - **Options:** Running, cycling, swimming, brisk walking, or group fitness classes.\n   - **Intensity:** Moderate to vigorous intensity (aim for 60-80% of your maximum heart rate).\n   - **Duration:** 30-45 minutes.\n\n   **Example Weekly Schedule:**\n   - Monday: 30 minutes of running\n   - Wednesday: 45 minutes of cycling\n   - Friday: 30 minutes of swimming\n   - Sunday: 30 minutes of brisk walking or a group class\n\n2. **Strength Training (2-3 days/week)**\n   - **Focus:** Major muscle groups (legs, arms, back, core).\n   - **Options:** Bodyweight exercises (push-ups, squats, lunges), resistance bands, or weights.\n   - **Sets/Reps:** 3 sets of 10-15 reps for each exercise.\n\n   **Example Weekly Schedule:**\n   - Tuesday: Full body strength workout (squats, push-ups, lunges, planks)\n   - Thursday: Upper body strength (dumbbell rows, shoulder presses, tricep dips)\n   - Saturday: Lower body strength (deadlifts, step-ups, calf raises)\n\n3. **Flexibility and Recovery (Daily)**\n   - **Activities:** Stretching, yoga, or foam rolling.\n   - **Duration:** 10-15 minutes post-workout or on rest days.\n\n### Diet Plan\n\n**General Guidelines:**\n- Aim for a calorie deficit of about 500-1,000 calories per day for safe weight loss.\n- Focus on whole, unprocessed foods.\n- Stay hydrated (aim for at least 8 cups of water daily).\n\n**Proposed Daily Meal Plan:**\n\n**Breakfast:**\n- Option 1: Greek yogurt with berries and a sprinkle of granola.\n- Option 2: Oatmeal topped with sliced banana and a tablespoon of almond butter.\n\n**Snack:**\n- A piece of fruit (apple, banana, or pear) or a handful of nuts.\n\n**Lunch:**\n- Option 1: Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, and a vinaigrette dressing.\n- Option 2: Quinoa bowl with black beans, corn, diced bell peppers, and avocado.\n\n**Snack:**\n- Carrot sticks with hummus or a rice cake with almond butter.\n\n**Dinner:**\n- Option 1: Baked salmon with steamed broccoli and a side of brown rice.\n- Option 2: Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables served over cauliflower rice.\n\n**Snack (if needed):**\n- A small bowl of air-popped popcorn or a few squares of dark chocolate.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Track your food intake and exercise using an app or journal.\n- Get enough sleep (7-9 hours per night).\n- Avoid sugary drinks and limit alcohol consumption.\n- Be mindful of portion sizes.\n- Stay consistent and patient; results take time.\n\nRemember that individual needs vary, so adjust this plan based on your personal preferences, dietary restrictions, and lifestyle. Good luck on your journey to lose 10 pounds!",
